      "representation": "view",
      "value": "<p>Arbitrary Output Variables (AOVs) are the secondary images produced by the renderer. There can be any number of them generated simultaneously and each one may go to a different file, a different display driver, or use different pixel filter settings. In some cases, special pixel filter modes may be used to avoid mixing values from different samples in a non-sensical way; typically these select a single sample to be representative of the whole pixel.</p><p>Broadly speaking, AOVs in RIS fall into these main categories: built-in, integrator (global), custom, and <a class=\"unresolved\" href=\"#\">light path expressions</a>.</p><div class=\"confluence-information-macro confluence-information-macro-information conf-macro output-block\" data-hasbody=\"true\" data-macro-id=\"e96b2c16-2b0d-466a-bf19-00577b3ec308\" data-macro-name=\"info\"><span class=\"aui-icon aui-icon-small aui-iconfont-info confluence-information-macro-icon\"> </span><div class=\"confluence-information-macro-body\"><p>For users interested in what is typically referred to as &quot;render passes&quot; for compositing a beauty image, look at the page on <a class=\"unresolved\" href=\"#\">light path expressions (LPE)</a>.</p></div></div><h2 class=\"auto-cursor-target\" id=\"AOVsinBlender-AOVsManager\">AOVs Manager</h2><p>By default, RenderMan for Blender will attempt to translate the default outputs that come with Blender. <br/><br/>If you click on the view layer properties <span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-thumbnail\" height=\"26\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639742/view_layers.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432722594&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=26&amp;height=26\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/view_layers.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432722594&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639756\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"view_layers.png\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/png\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"6ba6bf6f-b93f-4029-b98f-79a81911aa41\" data-media-type=\"file\" srcset=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639742/view_layers.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432722594&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=26&amp;height=26 2x, https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/thumbnails/544639742/view_layers.png?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432722594&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2&amp;width=26&amp;height=26 1x\"></span>, the UI should more or less look familiar to veteran users.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723005&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_1.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723005&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639777\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManForBlender_AOVs_1.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"3e7609e5-fc2b-4b97-96a2-c96b41d74a7b\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/></p><p>However, we can switch over to using RendeMan for Blender's AOVs manager by clicking on &quot;Switch to RenderMan Displays&quot; and after clicking the button, the UI will look like this:</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723005&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_2.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723005&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639780\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManForBlender_AOVs_2.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"3ae51bea-451a-4a99-abaf-44b9e23018ba\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px;\">The button will also attempt to create the equivalent AOVs from the outputs selected from the previous UI.<br/></span><span style=\"letter-spacing: 0.0px;\">Each item under the AOVs list is a single output with a number of channels.</span></p><p><br/><br/>Selecting an item from the list will display the file format options for that AOV along with the channels.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_3.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639783\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManForBlender_AOVs_3.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"57106436-0003-490c-96c0-c78dd873c3a8\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p><p>Here we can see dspy_2 will output to OpenEXR. <br/>Opening the openexr Settings section will show the options for the OpenEXR display driver, such as compression and the type (float or half float). <br/><br/>Camera allows you to render the AOV from a different camera than the main scene camera. The Denoise option will tell RenderMan to denoise the AOV during external/batch rendering. </p><p><br/><br/>To add channels to the AOV, use the Add Channel drop-down menu.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_4.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639786\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManForBlender_AOVs_4.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"c2a27175-1a79-4f22-89f4-20ffba71e6da\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span><br/><br/></p><p>You can remove a channel from an AOV by clicking on Delete Channel.<br/><br/><br/>Selecting a channel will also present a list of options that modify the behavior of the channel. It also shows the type and the source.</p><p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image\" loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-image-src=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/544639742/RenderManForBlender_AOVs_5.jpg?version=1&amp;modificationDate=1754432723174&amp;cacheVersion=1&amp;api=v2\" data-unresolved-comment-count=\"0\" data-linked-resource-id=\"544639789\" data-linked-resource-version=\"1\" data-linked-resource-type=\"attachment\" data-linked-resource-default-alias=\"RenderManForBlender_AOVs_5.jpg\" data-base-url=\"https://renderman.atlassian.net/wiki\" data-linked-resource-content-type=\"image/jpeg\" data-linked-resource-container-id=\"544639742\" data-linked-resource-container-version=\"1\" data-media-id=\"ac05b815-a366-442d-af44-e42a35792260\" data-media-type=\"file\"></span></p><p>You can also create your own custom channel by clicking on Custom from the Add Channel dropdown. <br/>It is then up to you to give the channel a name, the type, and the source (Light Path Expression).</p><p><br/></p><p><br/></p>"
    }
  },
